{"body": "+1\r\n\r\nIt is a mistake to instantiate a subclass of `HashWithIndifferentAccess` in the `new_from_hash_copying_default` method when you know (by definition) nothing about that subclass. Subclasses can always override `new_from_hash_copying_default` or `replace` if they need to. ", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/20040144", "created_at": "2013-06-26T11:12:54Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11089#issuecomment-20040144", "updated_at": "2013-06-26T11:12:54Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 11089, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdemare/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdemare/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdemare/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdemare", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdemare/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/mdemare", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdemare/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/ca8de10d3bafa1a9586a38e60d883a90?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ffa131721954c3ddae16ee67620ffb2e0.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdemare/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdemare/received_events", "gravatar_id": "ca8de10d3bafa1a9586a38e60d883a90", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdemare/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "mdemare", "type": "User", "id": 4588, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdemare/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523c9c3abd354364b9001a3d"}, "id": 20040144, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11089"}
